Welcome! I'm here to help you understand your relationship with money. This is a safe, judgment-free space for honest reflection.

Let's begin with your money story...
I'm currently a broke ass college student please help me ahhhh
What does financial success mean to you personally?

Financial success personally means to me that I'm going to be having tons of passive income without working boring 9-5s and wondering how I am going to pay my rent food and etc that apply especially emergency funds that go wrong. Basically passive income for personal freedom and for lifeline necessessities to support myself and potentially family people I love
When you think about your future, what matters most?
What matters most is going to have personal freedom in my life in terms of money and socially so I won't die alone
What feeling are you chasing when you think about having your finances figured out?
I think that I just want to feel secure overall and not that nervous. Informed for sure but not nervous in potentially being behind in the future
When you think about money, what emotion comes up most often?
Depends if I'm broke which I am most of the time I feel nevous and my stomach lumps but if I get a lot then i don't feel that different
When do you feel most stressed about money?
Paying rent for the statement from the bank that comes most often or if there's an opportunity but I don't know if i could go or not
Is there a money decision you're avoiding right now? What makes it hard to face?

trying to cancel subscriptions for actually helpful ai tools becasue they're helpful but then another moment I don't need them anymore and I can bootstrap later - just overall overestimating when i need lovable and supabase the most for buliding tbh
